                                                                  9228 1451   10
 Consistent independent and cumulative yield libraries            9228 1451   11
 Ternary fission and isomeric splitting included from JEFF-3.3    9228 1451   12
                                                                  9228 1451   13
 The thermal fission yield evaluation is based on the mixed       9228 1451   14
 method from the CEA-Cadarache and NNL collaboration consisting   9228 1451   15
 in the coupling of a new evaluation of mass yields and chain     9228 1451   16
 yields starting from experimental data without any model inputs  9228 1451   17
 (Ref 1). The methodology used for the fission yield evaluation   9228 1451   18
 is described in (Refs 1,2). The isotopic distributions come from 9228 1451   19
 the JEFF-3.3 library (Ref 3) adding the uncertainty propagation  9228 1451   20
 due to conservation laws and the self-normalization of fission   9228 1451   21
 yields. Consistent covariance matrices for independent and       9228 1451   22
 cumulative yields are available.                                 9228 1451   23
 Fission yields evaluations for epithermal (400 keV) and fast     9228 1451   24
 (14 MeV) neutron energies are unchanged compared to JEFF-3.3.    9228 1451   25
